<br />
If you want extra battlefields for Ferocity, take out Chamber first.    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship<br />
<br />
The idea is fairly simple, and very effective if played well.<br />
<br />
Tokens are either won or already there, and everyone dominates when there are tokens out. I&#39;ve included Eomer because he is a beast in combat, and so instead of just using all 4 gondor events as the healing one, I&#39;ve included 2 of each token event, so that Eomer gets stronger > adds to conditions > Aragons kills everyone in regroup if necessary.<br />
<br />
This deck dominates in every phase except the manuever, and suffers under archery. That&#39;s why Frodo has a vitality ring!!!<br />
<br />
Get the 5 companions visible as quickly as possible, along with at least one condition (but more helps) and you will win.<br />
<br />
Minions<br />
<br />
What can I say? archers wound and berserkers use them to win. Machines there to help berserkers go nuts, and archers add to machines. Devilry of Orthanc is good, so long as berserkers are out there.<br />
<br />
Take a shadow phase as an example,<br />
<br />
you&#39;ve got a weapons of isengard, two siege engines and a devilry.<br />
<br />
You play a uruk crossbow troop.<br />
<br />
siege engines give you two tokens, weapons of isengard gives you one (as is an archer) and the minion itself gives you one. thats four tokens out there.<br />
<br />
Then you can exert this minion (as it doens&#39;t have an archery special ability) to add a token to devilry. Thats four tokens on devilry and one on weapons of isengard. All from one minion! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
